                            <h3>Curriculum</h3>
                                <p>PMBA classes meet Monday &amp; Thursday evenings, 6:00-9:50 p.m., at the Executive Development Center’s state-of-the-art downtown facility. Per the rotational schedule, they also meet at UCF’s Regional Campuses in Daytona, Palm Bay, and Valencia West.</p>

<p>The 39-credit hour curriculum comprises six sessions over 24 months and provides students with relevant knowledge in varied business areas. Core analytical courses build a solid foundation for advanced functional business topics. And capstone courses focus on “boardroom” leadership development and executive strategy.</p>

<p>View a list of courses currently taught in the PMBA.</p>

